            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "I couldn't find an existing way in Lua to cleanly detach another UI. `vim.fn.chanclose(chan)` gets close, but doesn't set `chan->detach`, so if one of the others is a stdio UI (e.g. an --embed parent), closing it exits the server.\r\n\r\n`nvim_ui_detach` and `nvim__chan_set_detach` are FUNC_API_REMOTE_ONLY, so Lua can only invoke them against the caller's own channel.\r\n\r\nTo move this to `_core/server.lua`, I'd need to add a new primitive (something like `nvim__ui_detach(chan)`) that sets `chan->detach = true`, sends `error_exit`, and closes the channel.\r\n\r\nDoes this sound correct, or do you have a different approach in mind?",
            "commit_id": "246156ff16aa4507c5f71b1b75ae5df23f10da89",
            "created_at": "2026-04-20T05:36:04Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -108,6 +108,40 @@ void remote_ui_disconnect(uint64_t channel_id, Error *err, bool send_error_exit)\n   remote_ui_destroy(ui);\n }\n \n+/// Detaches all UIs except the one on `keep_channel_id`.\n+void remote_ui_disconnect_others(uint64_t keep_channel_id)",
